---
title: Magnetic Button
description: A button with a dramatic lift and shadow on hover using CSS transitions and `@starting-style`.
slug: magnetic-button
cssFile: magnetic-button.css
explanation: "The lift effect uses `transform: translateY(-6px) scale(1.04)` on `:hover` with a `cubic-bezier(0.34, 1.56, 0.64, 1)` timing function — the Y₂ value above 1.0 creates a spring overshoot. A `box-shadow` with a large blur and spread grows on hover to simulate the button floating above the surface. `@starting-style` defines where the animation begins when the element first enters the DOM, creating a smooth entrance."
---
{% extends "example.njk" %}
{% block demo %}
<div class="mag-btns">
	<button class="mag-btn mag-btn-primary">Primary</button>
	<button class="mag-btn mag-btn-sky">Blue</button>
	<button class="mag-btn mag-btn-ghost">Ghost</button>
</div>
{% endblock %}

{% block html_code %}
{%- highlight "html" %}
<button class="mag-btn">Hover me</button>
{%- endhighlight %}
{% endblock %}

{% block css_code %}
{%- highlight "css" %}
.mag-btn {
  transition:
    transform .3s cubic-bezier(0.34, 1.56, 0.64, 1),
    box-shadow .3s ease;
}

.mag-btn:hover {
  transform: translateY(-6px) scale(1.04);
  box-shadow: 0 16px 40px rgba(184, 255, 87, .35);
}

@starting-style {
  .mag-btn {
    transform: translateY(10px);
    opacity: 0;
  }
}
{%- endhighlight %}
{% endblock %}
